Q4 QUANTUM PROCESSING UNIT (QPU)

Technology: Superconducting transmon qubits, flip-chip packaging.
Qubit count: 128 physical qubits (scalable to 1024).
Gate fidelity: >99.9% single-qubit, >99.5% two-qubit.
Control system: Cryo-CMOS waveform generators at 4 K stage.
Interface: FPGA-based Quantum Translator with zero-copy DMA
           over PCIe Gen6 (128 GB/s).
Software stack: Qiskit backend provider, OpenQASM 3.0 support.

Use cases: Quantum chemistry, QUBO optimization, Shor/Grover
           algorithms, variational quantum eigensolvers.

Note: The QPU is designed to be co-packaged with an AnalogX1000
      chiplet via the photonic interconnect for hybrid quantum-
      classical workloads.
